# 13. アイドルの資格

Airi: Sorry you had to see that, Minori. Haruka.
Minori: Don't worry about it. I'm just glad nobody was hurt!
Haruka: .....
Airi: Shizuku, I'm sorry. I was only thinking about myself. I don't expect you to forgive me, but...
Airi: I'm truly sorry for everything.
Shizuku: Airi...
Shizuku: Airi, could I ask you a favor?
Airi: Huh?
Shizuku: I want you to be an idol again.
Airi: What?!
Shizuku: What you said back there made me really happy. I realized there really was someone who actually saw me as I was.
Shizuku: With just a few words, you managed to fill me with hope.
Airi: But—
Shizuku: Airi, you are and always were an idol. The one who told me what I needed to hear to make it through the tough times. The one who showed me the dream of becoming a true idol.
Shizuku: That was all you, Airi.
Airi: !!
Shizuku: That's why I'm sure you can give even more hope to others.
Shizuku: I want to see that Airi again.
Airi: .....
Airi: You can be so unfair sometimes, Shizuku...
Shizuku: What? I can?
Airi: I can't very well say no to you after all that.
Shizuku: Does that mean...
Airi: You're going to join me, though!
Shizuku: Huh?
Airi: You did say I'm the one who showed you the dream of becoming a true idol, didn't you?
Airi: If that's your dream, then you can't give up!
Shizuku: !!
Airi: I may be your idol, but you're mine as well!
Airi: It's frustrating never measuring up to you, but I still want to see you standing up on stage!
Airi: I can't return to being an idol knowing I was the reason you stopped being one.
Shizuku: Airi...
Shizuku: All right. We'll do this together then, Airi.
Airi: !!
Shizuku: I'd always hoped we could be idols together someday.
Shizuku: We may have given up our dream once, but I feel like we can make it this time so long as we're together.
Airi: Shizuku...
Airi: Okay! This time, I promise not to give up!
Airi: Let's do it, Shizuku.
Shizuku: Yeah. Let's give it our best, Airi!
Airi: Wh-What are you doing?! Don't glom onto me!
Minori: Momoi, Hinomori. I'm so happy for both of you.
Haruka: .....
Shizuku: Hehe. I can't believe I get to be an idol with Airi! It's like a dream come true!
Airi: Okay, if we're going to do this, then let's make sure to be the best! We'll give our fans more hope than anyone else can!
Shizuku: Of course!
Airi: We have a lot to think about, though, like what agencies might accept us and the logistics of everything.
Airi: I guess we should probably practice together first. How about we start tomorrow after school up on the roof?
Minori: What? Really?!
Shizuku: That would be wonderful. But are you sure we won't be in the way, Minori?
Minori: O-Of course not! I'd love for you both to come!
Airi: Haruka, um... Would you like to practice with us every once in a while?
Airi: To be honest, I'd love a few pointers. I've been watching you since you were in ASRUN. You were always the best of the best, and I'd like to get back into form ASAP.
Haruka: Sorry, but I'll have to pass.
Shizuku: I'd like it if you joined us, as well. If we had Haruka to help teach us, I'm sure...
Haruka: .....!
???: Please! If you helped teach me, I'm sure I could improve!
Haruka: Stop it. I have no right to be an idol.
Minori: ...What?
Haruka: !!
Airi: What do you mean you don't have the right?
Haruka: ...Nothing. I misspoke. It's nothing.
Shizuku: Haruka?
Haruka: Please don't worry about me. I just want to be a regular student.
Haruka: But good luck, you three. I'll be cheering for you.
Minori: Haruka, wait!
Airi: What she said...meant something, didn't it?
Shizuku: Haruka... I wonder if something happened.
Minori: (Haruka doesn't have the right to be an idol?)
Minori: (Why would she think that?)
